The paper deals with improving the robustness of machine reading comprehension models, which is a topic that falls under natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). The use of external linguistic knowledge and regularization techniques are also common in NLP and AI research. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves neural models, which are a common topic in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research, making cs.LG and cs.NE likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper uses RC models to analyze text, which is a common application of computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV is also a possible sub-category.
